27/12/2002
ATHENS, Greece -- The Archbishopric introduced services in languages other than Greek on Thursday (26 December). Christmas services were conducted in Albanian and Romanian at two churches, while New Year's and Epiphany services in both languages will take place next month. A third church will conduct Russian Orthodox Christmas services in Russian on 7 January and Epiphany services on 19 January, in accordance with the Julian calendar. (Kathimerini - 27/12/02)
